@itajaja 

The idea here is that, when using a cursor-based pagination, instead of trying to figure out the sorting from the `query`, we just look at `view.sorting`, and ask it how `query` is sorted.

It lets us remove a lot of crummy logic from the cursor pagination implementation, and is more robust to sorting on things like hybrid expressions that aren't columns.

